<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-083-019 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 192 789</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  August 12 1991 n364 p20(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EDI centralization: groups forming to coordinate plans.andO;(electronic data interchange)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Foley, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>As the popularity of electronic communications systems such asE-mail, electronic funds transfer systems (EFTS) and electronicdata interchange (EDI) increases, there is a concomitant need incorporations to improve the management of these systems.andP;  TheGartner Group recommends establishing a committee to oversee anorganization's use of what it calls inter-enterprise systems.andP;  TheGartner Group points out that E-mail, EDI and EFTS systems oftencome into being in an organization on the departmental level, withno central planning or control.andP;  Without central control,organizations run into compatibility problems and wasted resourcesif efforts are duplicated in several different departments.andP;  TheGartner Group recommends that the oversight committee be made upof information systems personnel as well as representatives fromthe individual departments.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MISOrganization StructureCentralizationEFTSElectronic mail systemsElectronic data interchange.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>